    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-08T10:23:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-01T11:00:00-05:00" n="466"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d466">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3436: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName> [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1920-08-08T11:23:00-04:00"
                            notBefore="1920-08-02T00:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>].<lb/>[Received August 8, 1920—11:23 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>215. Presidential mandate dissolves all branches of the Anfu Club and also the
                    15th division of the regular Army which assisted Tuan. Tsao Kun and Chang Tso
                    Lin are now in Peking conferring with the President.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
